lass=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">i_le_j</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">trans</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j_le</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Embedding</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">trans_apply</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- Hall's universal group... maybe?</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DirectLimit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Γ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Γ_embed</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is <code>U</code> Hall's universal group? If not, how would one go about defining it?</p>",
